  "texts": [
    "When employing different decoder networks, conventional Transpose Convolution yields satisfactory results.",
    "However, Resize & Convolution demonstrate advantages in pixel-level predictions.",
    "We speculate that this is due to the limited impact of the chessboard effect on the whole crack detection but a larger influence on pixel-level predictions.",
    "It's worth noting that even though we included a model with an upsampling decoder, it can be understood as employing fully connected layers for decoding.",
    "While this approach omits an upsampling decoder network and still achieves around 80% accuracy, its performance remains weaker than the upsampling version."
